Document: PhysicalSkyMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_physicalskymaterial.rst
Summary: Describes the PhysicalSkyMaterial, which uses the Preetham analytic daylight model for realistic sky rendering, taking sun properties from a DirectionalLight3D.

The PhysicalSkyMaterial uses the Preetham analytic daylight model to draw a sky based on physical properties. This results in a substantially more realistic sky than the ProceduralSkyMaterial, but it is slightly slower and less flexible.

The PhysicalSkyMaterial only supports one sun. The color, energy, and direction of the sun are taken from the first DirectionalLight3D in the scene tree.
---CHUNK---
Document: PhysicalSkyMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_physicalskymaterial.rst
Summary: Defines the properties that control the appearance of a physical sky material.

Properties
- energy_multiplier (float): Multiplies the sky's energy. Default: 1.0
- ground_color (Color): The color of the ground. Default: Color(0.1, 0.07, 0.034, 1)
- mie_coefficient (float): Controls the scattering of light by Mie particles. Default: 0.005
- mie_color (Color): The color of light scattered by Mie particles. Default: Color(0.69, 0.729, 0.812, 1)
- mie_eccentricity (float): Controls the directionality of Mie scattering. Default: 0.8
- night_sky (Texture2D): A texture to use for the night sky.
- rayleigh_coefficient (float): Controls the scattering of light by Rayleigh particles. Default: 2.0
- rayleigh_color (Color): The color of light scattered by Rayleigh particles. Default: Color(0.3, 0.405, 0.6, 1)
- sun_disk_scale (float): Scales the size of the sun disk. Default: 1.0
- turbidity (float): Controls the amount of haze in the atmosphere. Default: 10.0
- use_debanding (bool): Enables or disables debanding to reduce color banding. Default: true
